	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(center)">&#40;Copy.&#41;</p>
				<p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Montreal</placeName> <date>23 April 5610</date></p>
				<p>Reverend and Dear Sir&#47;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">In reply to the commu&#45;<lb/>nication in which you convey to us your desire<lb/> of becoming a candidate for the office of Hazan<lb/> to the Portuguese congregation of <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>&#44; we<lb/> have to inform you that at a meeting held this<lb/> day&#44; it was unanimously resolved to convey to<lb/> you our full concurrence in the step you propose<lb/> taking&#44; and our best wishes for your success.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">At the same time&#44; we would express the deep<lb/> regret your communication has afforded us showing<lb/> as it did for the first time&#44; there existed a proba&#45;<lb/>bility of our losing your valuable services&#44; which<lb/> during a period of four years have given unmitiga<lb/>ted satisfaction to the whole of the congregation<lb/>  With an earnest wish to do every thing in our<lb/> power that might lead to advance your interests&#44;<lb/> and desirous of seeing you placed in that extend<lb/>ed sphere of usefulness the high order of your<lb/> talents unquestionably deserve&#44; but which our<lb/> <sic>comparitively</sic> small congregation does not afford<lb/> still cannot we but recollect that should you<lb/> be the successful candidate we will lose one<lb/> who by his conduct both in public and private<lb/> life&#44; has gained the love and respect of every<lb/> member of his congregation&#44; and who by his</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>attainments&#44; feelings&#44; and department&#44; we are<lb/> proud to say&#44; has commanded the esteem and<lb/> respect of our Christian fellow citizens&#44; and ac&#45;<lb/>quired a reputation and position not inferior<lb/> to any of their clergy</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">We would further&#44; Reverend Sir&#44; express<lb/> our regret at the prospect of being deprived&#44;<lb/> ourselves of the advantage of your able and<lb/> eloquent expositions of our holy religion&#44; and<lb/> our children of your useful and acceptable<lb/> Instructions in the language and faith of<lb/> our ancestors&#59; the school you have established<lb/> we shall ever regard as a memento of your<lb/> untiring zeal and abilities.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">In conclusion&#44; dear sir&#44; we would inform<lb/> you that under any circumstances your present<lb/> situation will remain open for you&#59; and express<lb/>ing our best wishes for your success and ad<lb/>vancement in life&#44; and although perhaps con&#45;<lb/>trary to your wishes&#44; hoping we may not so<lb/> soon be deprived of your valuable services<lb/> of which any congregation may be proud.</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)">We remain Reverend and Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">Your obedient Servants</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">Samuel Benjamin</persName> President</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">John Levey</persName> Treasurer</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">Wm Benjamin</persName> Secretary</p>
				<p><persName role="author">A H David</persName> M. D.</p>
				<p><persName role="author">G I Ascher</persName></p>
				<p><persName role="author">David Moss</persName>.</p>
				<p rend="The following is written sideways between the columns of names.">Trustees</p>
				<p>To the <addressee>Rev. Abraham De Sola</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">&#38;c &#38;c &#38;c</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>&#40;The original of the present letter is<lb/> in the possession of <persName>A Hart Esqr</persName><lb/> Parnass K. K. Mikveh Israel.&#8221;&#41;</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p rend="align(center)"><hi rend="underline">Testimonials</hi></p>
				<p rend="align(center)">To</p>
				<p rend="align(center)"><persName>Abraham De Sola</persName></p>
				<p rend="align(center)">from his</p>
				<p rend="align(center)">Congregation at <placeName>Montreal</placeName></p>
				<p rend="align(center)"><hi rend="underline"><date>April 23&#44; 5610</date></hi></p>
